==Old English==

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /hwæt/
===Etymology===
Common Germanic *''[[hwa-]]'', from an Indo-European base ''*kuos, *kuod''. Cognates include Old Frisian [[hwet]], Old Saxon [[hwat]] (Dutch [[wat]]), Old High German [[hwaz]] (German [[was]]), Old Norse [[hvat]] (Swedish [[vad]]), Gothic [[𐍈𐌰]]. The Indo-European root also led to Latin ''[[quod]]'' and Lithuanian [[kàd]].

===Pronoun===
'''hwæt'''

# [[what]]

===Interjection===
'''hwæt'''

# [[what]]!, [[listen]]!

===Adverb===
'''hwæt'''

# [[now]], [[indeed]]

